<paragraphs xml:id="dynamics-and-stability">
<title>Dynamics and stability</title>

<p> We see a hint of a <sq>stability condition</sq>
in the right-hand panel. Recall that equilibria occur where the diagonal
and updating functions cross. The equilibrium point is
<term>stable</term> if the updating function is <sq>not too steep</sq>
at this point, and <term>unstable</term> if the updating function is
<sq>too steep</sq> at this point.<!-- linebreak -->What might we mean by
<sq>too steep</sq>? How can we describe the <sq>steepness</sq> of a
graph at a point?
</p>

</paragraphs>

